# Feature Progress Tracking Rule

## Primary Progress Source

- Store feature progress files under `docs/features/progress/`.
- Use one progress file per feature, named as `<feature-name>.md` (example: `dating-app.md`).
- Treat the feature progress file as the single source of truth.
- Before implementation, quickly check the progress file and identify:
  - current in-progress track / module / section
  - completed tasks
  - next must-pass story or acceptance item

## Update Discipline

- After every small completed task, update the matching file under `docs/features/progress/` in the same session.
- Mark tasks with clear checkbox status (`[ ]` / `[x]`) and keep wording specific.
- If scope changes, add/adjust tasks first, then continue coding.

## Student-Facing Progress Output

- In each substantial reply, include:
  - what was finished this step
  - what remains next
  - which active workstream is in progress (for example: `SEC-*`, `API-*`, `DATA-*`, `TEST-*`, `OPS-*`, or custom labels)
- When blocked, explicitly state blocker + required input.

## State Matrix Enforcement

- Any UI work must map to `loading / empty / error / success` states.
- Do not mark a section done until its state matrix coverage is reflected in `todo.md`.
